What you need to know:

With points certain to be dropped by one of the title contenders at Anfield this weekend, third placed Manchester City can climb back into the raceManchester United head to Anfield knowing they have a golden opportunity to open up a potentially priceless six-point lead over Jurgen Klopp's menCity's 1-0 win against Brighton on Wednesday extended their unbeaten run to 14 games in all competitions and left them just four points behind United with a game in hand